"{\"uid\": \"rferl.org-a-russia-france-macron-olympics-threat-32891053.html\", \"text\": \"Share  Share  Print  French President Emmanuel Macron said on April 4 that he has no doubt Russia will malevolently target the Paris Olympics this summer. \\\"I have no doubt whatsoever, including in terms of information,\\\" Macron said in response to a question about whether he thought that Russia would try to target the Olympics. Macron's comments represent his most explicit acknowledgment to date of foreign threats to the security or smooth running of the games. The games will take place amid a complex global backdrop, including Russia's war in Ukraine and Israel's conflict with Hamas, which has been designated a terrorist organization by the United States and the European Union.    RFE/RL has been declared an \\\"undesirable organization\\\" by the Russian government.  If you are in Russia or the Russia-controlled parts of Ukraine and hold a Russian passport or are a stateless person residing permanently in Russia or the Russia-controlled parts of Ukraine, please note that you could face fines or imprisonment for sharing, liking, commenting on, or saving our content, or for contacting us.  To find out more,click here.  Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty \\u00a9 2025 RFE/RL, Inc. All Rights Reserved.\"}"